my stomach is upset from
swallowing the drip meant
for my nose. evening
approaches and i'm alone
on the couch.

the many sins of my
youth are with me here,
laughing in my ears. i
ignore them, but they don't
listen to my silence.

yet the notes of the score
seem dissonant, still,
forgotten. how i long to
hear your voice crying for
my soul, wishing me home.
